# Step-by-Step POC Using Hardened Images

---

# Step 1 — Replace Runtime Image with Hardened Image

Instead of:

```dockerfile id="tjlwm0"
FROM openjdk:17-jdk
```

Use hardened minimal image:

```dockerfile id="jlwmv3"
FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine
```

---

# Why Better?

| Improvement     | Benefit                |
| --------------- | ---------------------- |
| Alpine Linux    | Smaller image          |
| JRE only        | No compiler tools      |
| Fewer packages  | Fewer CVEs             |
| Minimal runtime | Smaller attack surface |

---

# Step 2 — Create Hardened Dockerfile

Use this improved Dockerfile.

```dockerfile id="jlwm3y"
# =========================
# Build Stage
# =========================
FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS build

WORKDIR /app

COPY pom.xml .
COPY src ./src

RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests

# =========================
# Runtime Stage (Hardened)
# =========================
FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine

WORKDIR /app

# Create non-root user
RUN addgroup -S appgroup && adduser -S appuser -G appgroup

COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar

# Change ownership
RUN chown -R appuser:appgroup /app

# Run as non-root
USER appuser

EXPOSE 8080

CMD ["java", "-jar", "app.jar"]
```

